This fixture is a Go module split across two files in one package. main.go
references a function declared in lib.go. goto-definition on the reference must
resolve into lib.go, exercising gopls cross-file workspace resolution.

Markers embedded in the source drive the test:

  query=Greeting  marks the identifier occurrence to query, in main.go.
  target=Greeting marks the declaration the definition must resolve to, in
                  lib.go. The resolved target URI must therefore be lib.go, not
                  the queried main.go.

The harness reads these markers to compute query and expected-target positions
and to identify the file each marker lives in.

-- go.mod --
module definitioncrossfile

go 1.27

-- main.go --
package main

func main() {
	println(Greeting()) // query=Greeting
}

-- lib.go --
package main

func Greeting() string { // target=Greeting
	return "hello"
}
